SRC: 老年人和青少年的金融素养水平相对较低 ， “ 一老一少”仍将是金融教育持续关注的重点对象；尼尔森发布的《中国年轻人负债状况报告》及央视财经发布的《2019-2020中国青年消费报告》显示，年轻一代具有巨大的消费潜力，信用消费成为消费升级重要途径，86.6%的年轻人都在使用信贷产品，近半数人没有债务累积，年轻一代虽然整体呈现理性消费趋势，虽与外界贴上的“过度挥霍”标签大相径庭，但部分年轻人的确存在过度消费、跟风消费行为，并因此产生了过大的财务压力和债务风险，甚至导致社会问题逐渐增加，金融企业应勇于承担社会责任，进行正向引导。

SRC: 老年人和青少年的金融素养水平相对较低 ， “ 一老一少”仍将是金融教育持续关注的重点对象；尼尔森发布的《中国年轻人负债状况报告》及央视财经发布的《2019-2020中国青年消费报告》显示，年轻一代具有巨大的消费潜力，信用消费成为消费升级重要途径，86.6%的年轻人都在使用信贷产品，近半数人没有债务累积，年轻一代虽然整体呈现理性消费趋势，虽与外界贴上的“过度挥霍”标签大相径庭，但部分年轻人的确存在过度消费、跟风消费行为，并因此产生了过大的财务压力和债务风险，甚至导致社会问题逐渐增加，金融企业应勇于承担社会责任，进行正向引导。
HYP: The financial literacy level of the elderly and teenagers is relatively low, and "one old and one young" will remain the focus of financial education; According to the Report on the Debt Status of Chinese Youth released by Nielsen and the Report on the Consumption of Chinese Youth 2019-2020 released by CCTV Finance, The younger generation has great consumption potential, Credit consumption has become an important way to upgrade consumption, 86.6% of young people are using credit products, Nearly half of the people have no debt accumulation, Although the younger generation presents a rational consumption trend as a whole, Although it is quite different from the label of "excessive profligacy" labeled by the outside world, some young people do have excessive consumption and follow-up consumption behavior, which leads to excessive financial pressure and debt risk, and even leads to the gradual increase of social problems. Financial enterprises should be brave enough to assume social responsibility and give positive guidance.

HYP: The financial literacy level of the elderly and young people is relatively low, and "one old and one young" will continue to be the focus of financial education; Nielsen's "China Youth Debt Status Report" and CCTV Finance's "2019-2020 China Youth Consumption Report" show that the younger generation has huge consumption potential. Credit consumption has become an important way to upgrade consumption, 86.6% of young people are using credit products, and nearly half of them have no debt accumulation, although the younger generation shows an overall trend of rational consumption, although it is very different from the label of "excessive spending", some young people do have excessive consumption, follow the trend of consumption behavior, and therefore This has led to excessive financial pressure and debt risks, and has even led to an increase in social problems, so financial companies should be brave enough to assume social responsibility and provide positive guidance.
